abstract: KEY WEST, Fla., April 1.--No facts are known here concerning the reported filibustering expedition against Cuba. The reports are regarded as mere rumors. abstract: CITY OF MEXICO, April 2.--In the United National and Mercantile Banks the former has five local Directors and the latter ten. The Government has encouraged the fusion, and the consolidated banks can if they desire have the settlement of the national debt.

abstract: WATERBURY, Conn., April 3.--Benjamin Bissell, a farmer, was stopped by three teamsters at Torrington, on Monday, and assaulted for blocking the road. He defended himself with a cart-stake, and whipped all three, being himself badly beaten. James McCone, one of the teamsters, has since died, and is found to have his skull fractured in many places by Bissell's blows. Bissell is sick in bed, and the inquest has been adjourned until next Tuesday.

The affair occurred in Tracy's saloon. They had been skylarking, and Tracy, taking up a revolver, almost it at Ethier's heart, and pulled the trigger. The latter fell dead without uttering a word. The pistol had been loaded during the day without Tracy's knowledge.

abstract: LONDON, April 22.--At 9:30 o'clock this morning an earthquake shock of considerable force was felt in the eastern counties of England. Localities in Essex and Suffolk were the scenes of great disturbance. The railway station was partially destroyed.

abstract: At the meeting of the stockholders of the Academy of Music on Monday evening some very hard words were said against Col. Mapleson. It became apparent that if he gives opera in the house next season he will have to do it without any guarantee by the stockholders, unless a great chance of sentiment is effected between now and then.

abstract: CLEVELAND, Ohio, April 29.--Congressman Abram S. Hewitt and his brother-in-law, ex-Mayor Edward Cooper, of New-York City, to-day began suit in the United States Circuit Court in Cleveland against the Cleveland Rolling Mill Company for $200,000 damages for alleged infringement of a patent.
